register.description: This register contains the IP revision code

bitfield.description: IP revision [7:4] Major revision [3:0] Minor revision Examples: 0x10 for 1.0, 0x21 for 2.1

register.description: This register controls the various parameters of the OCP interface

bitfield.description: Write 0's for future compatibility. Reads returns 0
Software reset. Set this bit to trigger a module reset. The bit is automatically reset by the hardware. During reads, it always returns 0.

bitenum.description: Automatic OCP clock gating strategy is applied, bnased on the OCP interface activity

register.description: This register provides status information about the module

bitfield.description: Reserved for OCP socket status information Read returns 0

register.description: This register supplies the currently active IRQ interrupt number.
This register supplies the currently active FIQ interrupt number
This register contains the new interrupt agreement bits

bitfield.description: Write 0's for future compatibility. Reads returns 0
Reset FIQ output and enable new FIQ generation

bitenum.description: Reset FIQ output and enable new FIQ generation
Reset IRQ output and enable new IRQ generation

register.description: This register controls protection of the other registers. This register can only be accessed in priviledged mode, regardless of the curent value of the protection bit.

bitfield.description: Write 0's for future compatibility. Reads returns 0

bitenum.description: Protection mode enabled. When enabled, only priviledged mode can access registers.

register.description: This register controls the clock auto-idle for the functional clock and the input synchronisers

bitfield.description: Write 0's for future compatibility. Reads returns 0

bitenum.description: Input synchroniser clock is free running (default)
Input synchroniser clock is auto-gated based on interrupt input activity
Functional clock gating strategy is applied (default)

register.description: This register supplies the currently active IRQ priority level
This register supplies the currently active FIQ priority level
This register sets the priority threshold

bitfield.description: Priority threshold (used values 0x00-0x1f or 0x00-0x3f, 0xff disables the threshold).

register.description: This register shows the raw interrupt input status before masking
This register contains the interrupt mask
This register is used to clear the interrupt mask bits.

bitfield.description: Write 1 clears the mask bit to 0, reads return 0

register.description: This register is used to set the interrupt mask bits.

bitfield.description: Write 1 sets the mask bit to 1, reads return 0

register.description: This register is used to set the software interrupt bits. It is also used to read the currently active software interrupts.

bitfield.description: Reads returns the currently active software interrupts, Write 1 sets the software interrupt bits to 1

register.description: This register is used to clear the software interrupt bits

bitfield.description: Write 1 clears the sofware interrupt bits to 0, reads return 0
